{"QUAKE":[{"def":"To be agitated with quick, short motions continually repeated; to shake with fear, cold, etc.","pos":""},{"def":"To shake, vibrate, or quiver, either from not being solid, as soft, wet land, or from violent convulsion of any kind; as, the earth quakes; the mountains quake.","pos":""}],"QUAKER":[{"def":"One of a religious sect founded by George Fox, of Leicestershire, England, about 1650, -- the members of which call themselves Friends.","pos":""}],"QUAKERESS":[{"def":"A woman who is a member of the Society of Friends.","pos":""}],"QUAKERISH":[{"def":"Like or pertaining to a Quaker; Quakerlike.","pos":""}],"QUAKERISM":[{"def":"The peculiar character, manners, tenets, etc.","pos":""}],"QUAKERLY":[{"def":"Resembling Quakers; Quakerlike; Quakerish.","pos":""}],"QUAKINESS":[{"def":"The state of being quaky; liability to quake.","pos":""}],"QUAKING":[{"def":"Briza, having slender-stalked and pendulous ovate spikelets, which quake and rattle in the wind.","pos":""}],"QUAKINGLY":[{"def":"In a quaking manner; fearfully.","pos":""}],"QUAKY":[{"def":"Shaky, or tremulous; quaking.","pos":""}]}